en I wanted to know something, I wanted it undistorted by somebody else's imperfect knowledge.\n\n- Milton\n|\nDo I wither up and disappear, or do I make the best of my time left?'-Morrie\n\n- Mitch Albom, Tuesdays with Morrie\n|\nIt is not the chains of some tyrant that robs us of freedom. Rather, it is the staleness of our attitude.\n\n- Craig\n|\nIt was in the reign of George II. that the above-named personages lived and quarrelled ; good or bad, handsome or ugly, rich or poor, they are all equal now\n\n- William Makepeace Thackeray, The Memoirs of Barry Lyndon, Esq. written by himself\n|\nManifesting is a lot like making a cake. The things needed are supplied by you, the mixing is done by your mind and the baking is done in the oven of the universe.\n\n- Stephen Richards, Think Your way to Success: Let Your Dreams Run Free\n|\nMy name is Jimmy,but my friends just call methe hideous penguin boy.\n\n- Tim Burton, The Melancholy Death of Oyster Boy and Other Stories\n|\ndo not let anyone inuntil they love you so fiercely,you have no defense against their love.\n\n- AVA., you are safe here.\n|\nHe wanted to heat up the truth, to make it burn so hot that you would feel exactly what he felt.\n\n- Tim\n|\nThe chief wonder of education is that it does not ruin everybody concerned in it, teachers and taught.\n\n- Henry Adams, The Education of Henry Adams\n|\nKnowledge speaks, but wisdom listens.\n\n- ~ Jimi Hendrix (1942-1970), musician"